            <h3 class="text-2xl fw-bold font-Syne leading-10">
              1. What is Self-Esteem?
            </h3>
            <p class="paragraph">
              Self-esteem is our overall sense of value and self-worth. It's how
              we judge ourselves and impacts everything from our decision-making
              to our relationships. High self-esteem leads to a more positive
              outlook on life, while low self-esteem can result in self-doubt
              and negativity.
            </p>
            <p class="paragraph mb-12">
              Change Your Narrative: Replace self-critical thoughts with
              positive affirmations. Focus on your strengths and achievements to
              build confidence.
            </p>
            <p class="paragraph mb-12">
              Explore and Develop Strengths: Identify and work on your
              strengths. Engaging in activities you love can help uncover your
              talents and boost self-esteem.
            </p>
            <p class="paragraph mb-12">
              Challenge Limiting Beliefs: Reframe negative thoughts and
              challenge any limiting beliefs that hold you back. Avoid
              perfectionism and comparisons with others.
            </p>
          </div>

