              2. Why Self-Esteem Matters:
            </h3>
            <p class="paragraph">
              Self-esteem is not just a personal issue; it has a significant
              impact on our mental and emotional health. People with high
              self-esteem tend to be more resilient, handle criticism better,
              and have healthier relationships. On the other hand, low
              self-esteem can lead to feelings of inadequacy, fear of failure,
              and even mental health disorders like depression and anxiety.
            </p>
            <p class="paragraph">
              Heal and Reflect: Address any past wounds that might be affecting
              your self-esteem. Practice self-compassion and visualize a
              healthier self-esteem.
            </p>
            <p class="paragraph">
              Practice Self-Care: Prioritize your physical and emotional
              well-being by engaging in activities that bring joy and
              replenishment.
            </p>
